title: HOSE1exo
treatment_protocol_ch1: Cellular RNA of A2780cisThe cells were washed with phosphate-buffered saline (PBS), and the culture medium was replaced with advanced Dulbecco’s modified Eagle’s medium for ES-2, SKOV3, CAOV3, OV-90, OAW42, COV362 and MCAS cells, advanced DMEM/Ham's F-12 medium for RMG-1, RUG-S and HOSE1-3 cells, or advanced RPMI medium for A2780, OVCAR3 and KURAMOCHI cells. In all cases, the cell culture medium contained antibiotic and antifungal drugs as well as 2 mM L-glutamine (but not FBS). After incubation for 48 h, the conditioned medium (CM) was collected and centrifuged at 2,000 x g for 10 min at 4°C. To thoroughly remove cellular debris, the supernatant was filtered through a 0.22-m filter (Millipore). The CM was then used for EV isolation. To prepare EVs, CM was ultracentrifuged at 35,000 rpm using a SW41Ti rotor for 70 min at 4°C. The pellets were washed with PBS, ultracentrifuged at 35,000 rpm using the SW41Ti rotor for 70 min at 4°C and resuspended in PBS.
growth_protocol_ch1: Human OvCa cell lines were purchased from the American Type Culture Collection (ATCC), the European Collection of Cell Cultures (ECACC) and the Japanese Collection of Research Bioresources (JCRB) cell bank. The SKOV3, OVCAR3, CAOV3, ES-2, and OC-90 lines were from the ATCC, the A2780, OAW42, and COV362 were from the ECACC, and the MCAS, RMG-1, RMUG-S, and KURAMOCHI lines were from JRCB. HOSE1-3 were kindly gifted from Dr. Tohru Kiyono (National Cancer Center, Tokyo, Japan). All cell lines were cultured in optimal medium according to the suppliers’ recommendations.
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted using QIAzol and the miRNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany) according to manufacturer’s protocols. RNA was quantified using a NanoDrop-1000 spectrophotometer and a Agilent 2100 bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, Calif.).
label_protocol_ch1: The miRNA Complete Labeling and Hyb Kit (Agilent Technologies)
hyb_protocol: Agilent one-color gene expression hyb/wash protocol
description: Total RNA extracted form exosomes, and 50 ng of RNA for analysis
data_processing: The scanned images were analyzed with Feature Extraction Software 10.7.3.1 (Agilent) using default parameters to obtain background subtracted and spatially detrended Processed Signal intensities.  Features flagged in Feature Extraction as Feature Non-uniform outliers were excluded.
contact_laboratory: Division of Molecular and Cellular Medicine
contact_department: Group for Research of Molecular Functions and Targets

title: RMUG-Sexo
treatment_protocol_ch1: Cellular RNA of A2780cisThe cells were washed with phosphate-buffered saline (PBS), and the culture medium was replaced with advanced Dulbecco’s modified Eagle’s medium for ES-2, SKOV3, CAOV3, OV-90, OAW42, COV362 and MCAS cells, advanced DMEM/Ham's F-12 medium for RMG-1, RUG-S and HOSE1-3 cells, or advanced RPMI medium for A2780, OVCAR3 and KURAMOCHI cells. In all cases, the cell culture medium contained antibiotic and antifungal drugs as well as 2 mM L-glutamine (but not FBS). After incubation for 48 h, the conditioned medium (CM) was collected and centrifuged at 2,000 x g for 10 min at 4°C. To thoroughly remove cellular debris, the supernatant was filtered through a 0.22-m filter (Millipore). The CM was then used for EV isolation. To prepare EVs, CM was ultracentrifuged at 35,000 rpm using a SW41Ti rotor for 70 min at 4°C. The pellets were washed with PBS, ultracentrifuged at 35,000 rpm using the SW41Ti rotor for 70 min at 4°C and resuspended in PBS.
growth_protocol_ch1: Human OvCa cell lines were purchased from the American Type Culture Collection (ATCC), the European Collection of Cell Cultures (ECACC) and the Japanese Collection of Research Bioresources (JCRB) cell bank. The SKOV3, OVCAR3, CAOV3, ES-2, and OC-90 lines were from the ATCC, the A2780, OAW42, and COV362 were from the ECACC, and the MCAS, RMG-1, RMUG-S, and KURAMOCHI lines were from JRCB. HOSE1-3 were kindly gifted from Dr. Tohru Kiyono (National Cancer Center, Tokyo, Japan). All cell lines were cultured in optimal medium according to the suppliers’ recommendations.

HOSE1-3 were kindly gifted from Dr. Tohru Kiyono (National Cancer Center, Tokyo, Japan). All cell lines were cultured in optimal medium according to the suppliers’ recommendations.
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted using QIAzol and the miRNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany) according to manufacturer’s protocols. RNA was quantified using a NanoDrop-1000 spectrophotometer and a Agilent 2100 bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Palo Alto, Calif.).
label_protocol_ch1: The miRNA Complete Labeling and Hyb Kit (Agilent Technologies)
hyb_protocol: Agilent one-color gene expression hyb/wash protocol
description: Total RNA extracted form cells, and 100 ng of RNA for analysis
data_processing: The scanned images were analyzed with Feature Extraction Software 10.7.3.1 (Agilent) using default parameters to obtain background subtracted and spatially detrended Processed Signal intensities.  Features flagged in Feature Extraction as Feature Non-uniform outliers were excluded.
contact_laboratory: Division of Molecular and Cellular Medicine
contact_department: Group for Research of Molecular Functions and Targets

title: OAW42cell
treatment_protocol_ch1: Cellular RNA of A2780cisThe cells were washed with phosphate-buffered saline (PBS), and the culture medium was replaced with advanced Dulbecco’s modified Eagle’s medium for ES-2, SKOV3, CAOV3, OV-90, OAW42, COV362 and MCAS cells, advanced DMEM/Ham's F-12 medium for RMG-1, RUG-S and HOSE1-3 cells, or advanced RPMI medium for A2780, OVCAR3 and KURAMOCHI cells. In all cases, the cell culture medium contained antibiotic and antifungal drugs as well as 2 mM L-glutamine (but not FBS). After incubation for 48 h, the conditioned medium (CM) was collected and centrifuged at 2,000 x g for 10 min at 4°C. To thoroughly remove cellular debris, the supernatant was filtered through a 0.22-m filter (Millipore). The CM was then used for EV isolation. To prepare EVs, CM was ultracentrifuged at 35,000 rpm using a SW41Ti rotor for 70 min at 4°C. The pellets were washed with PBS, ultracentrifuged at 35,000 rpm using the SW41Ti rotor for 70 min at 4°C and resuspended in PBS.
